 specifying the recipient of an automated email message.','','none'),(7003,'The message that should be sent. You may include placeholders like [node:title], [user:account-name], [user:display-name] and [comment:body] to represent data that will be different each time message is sent. Not all placeholders will be available in all contexts.','','none'),(7004,'The message to be displayed to the current user. You may include placeholders like [node:title], [user:account-name], [user:display-name] and [comment:body] to represent data that will be different each time message is sent. Not all placeholders will be available in all contexts.','','none'),(7005,'The Aggregator module is an on-site syndicator and news reader that gathers and displays fresh content from RSS-, RDF-, and Atom-based feeds made available across the web. Thousands of sites (particularly news sites and blogs) publish their latest headlines in feeds, using a number of standardized XML-based formats. For more information, see the <a href=\":aggregator-module\">online documentation for the Aggregator module</a>.','','none'),(7006,'Configuring the display of feed items','','none'),(7007,'Discarding old feed items','','none'),(7008,'A <a href=\":aggregator-opml\">machine-readable OPML file</a> of all feeds is available. OPML is an XML-based file format used to share outline-structured information such as a list of RSS feeds. Feeds can also be <a href=\":import-opml\">imported via an OPML file</a>.','','none'),(7009,'A working <a href=\":cron\">cron maintenance task</a> is required to update feeds automatically.','','none'),(7010,'Current feeds are listed below, and <a href=\":addfeed\">new feeds may be added</a>. For each feed, the <em>latest items</em> block may be enabled at the <a href=\":block\">blocks administration page</a>.','','none'),(7011,'@title feed','','none'),(7012,'No feeds available. <a href=\":link\">Add feed</a>.','','none'),(7013,'The parent website\'s description that comes from the @de